# Cursor Rules for TOLO Coffee Shop App

## Package Manager
- ALWAYS use `bun` as the package manager, never npm or yarn
- Use `bun install` for installing dependencies
- Use `bun run <script>` for running scripts
- Use `bun add <package>` for adding new dependencies
- Use `bun remove <package>` for removing dependencies

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Follow existing project structure and naming conventions
- Use React Native Unistyles for styling
- Use Lingui for internationalization
- Implement proper error handling with Sentry integration

## Expo Updates
- Updates are configured with fingerprint runtime policy
- Always capture update errors to Sentry with proper context
- Use channels for different environments (development, preview, production)
- Never create UI components for update status - keep updates silent

## Development
- Test on both iOS and Android platforms
- Use development builds for testing native changes
- Follow React Native best practices for performance